Microsoft Windows Server 
Sconfig to set computer name, ip, network, etc


How to create a new drive mapped to a share location

Open Group Policy Management Console

Create a new Group Policy Object (GPO) or edit an existing one that applies to the users you want to access it.

User Configuration > Preferences > Windows Settings > Drive Maps.

Right-click in the right pane and select New > Mapped Drive.

New Drive Properties
Set Action to Create
Set Location to share location
Set Drive Letter to S:
Check the Reconnect box
Set Label (optional)

Switch to the Common tab and select"Item-level targeting".
Click the Targeting button and add a new item:
Select New Item > Security Group


Link the gpo to the appropriate ou for your users.


